narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: This course was the culmination of the ABET Electrical engineering major - we focused on applying everything we had learned in a team-centric environment.
I developed the ability to interface with unique sensors and fuse their data streams in order to achieve a pre-specified objective.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: This course was pretty good - we had a lot of agency to do what we wanted individually. Unfortunately due to time constraints we weren't able to merge our work together as much as we had wanted, but I still learned a lot.

The weakness of this course was the lack of direction provided by Professor Kuc. He changed the direction/objective of the project almost every week. To improve this course, Professor Kuc must at the start of the term layout the objectives of the project and stick to them.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I would recommend this to anyone who wants an ABET EE degree.
I would not recommend this course to another student, unless Professor Kuc improves the structure of the course.
